46

00:02:46,250  -->  00:02:49,050
In one, it will be a character to token ID,

47

00:02:49,050  -->  00:02:52,410
and in the other one, it will be token ID to the character.

48

00:02:52,410  -->  00:02:53,750
Now having these maps,

49

00:02:53,750  -->  00:02:56,870
we can implement the encode and the code methods.

50

00:02:56,870  -->  00:02:58,470
To implement the encode method,

51

00:02:58,470  -->  00:03:01,950
we will iterate through every character in the input text,

52

00:03:01,950  -->  00:03:05,710
and we will get the token ID for this character using our map.

53

00:03:05,710  -->  00:03:09,105
We will append it to the list of token IDs.

54

00:03:09,105  -->  00:03:10,990
Having this list of token IDs,

55

00:03:10,990  -->  00:03:15,420
who will then convert it into a tensor using torch.tensor function.

56

00:03:15,420  -->  00:03:17,790
The code method will work very similarly.

57

00:03:17,790  -->  00:03:19,990
We will iterate through token IDs,

58

00:03:19,990  -->  00:03:22,090
and the token IDs will be a tensor.

59

00:03:22,090  -->  00:03:24,750
We first need to convert it into a list,

60

00:03:24,750  -->  00:03:26,290
and then for every token,

61

00:03:26,290  -->  00:03:28,510
we get the character for this token,

62

00:03:28,510  -->  00:03:30,870
we append it to a list of characters,

63

00:03:30,870  -->  00:03:32,930
and then we convert it into a string.

64

00:03:32,930  -->  00:03:34,330
For the vocabulary size,

65

00:03:34,330  -->  00:03:35,890
it will be very straightforward.

66

00:03:35,890  -->  00:03:38,890
We will just get the length of one of these maps,

67

00:03:38,890  -->  00:03:40,450
and they will have the same lens,

68

00:03:40,450  -->  00:03:44,170
and both of them will have the same number of characters in now,

69

00:03:44,170  -->  00:03:46,390
having our tokenizer implementation,

70

00:03:46,390  -->  00:03:52,010
let's create an instance of our tokenizer and provide the whole training dataset into it,

71

00:03:52,010  -->  00:03:53,530
we will get our tokenizer.

72

00:03:53,530  -->  00:03:55,090
Now having a tokenizer,

73

00:03:55,090  -->  00:04:00,890
let's try to encode the how world string into a list of token IDs.

74

00:04:00,890  -->  00:04:08,030
If we run it, we get a tensor with different token IDs for this input string.

75

00:04:08,030  -->  00:04:09,910
If you look closely, you will see that

76

00:04:09,910  -->  00:04:14,510
