77

00:04:14,510  -->  00:04:17,905
For every position where we had the L character.

78

00:04:17,905  -->  00:04:20,700
We now have token AD equal to 50.

79

00:04:20,700  -->  00:04:22,390
Having the list of tokens,

80

00:04:22,390  -->  00:04:25,875
we can also decode it using the decode method.

81

00:04:25,875  -->  00:04:29,870
If we pass the result of code into the decode method,

82

00:04:29,870  -->  00:04:31,510
we will get our string back.

83

00:04:31,510  -->  00:04:34,970
Now we can also get the vocabulary size, which was 65,

84

00:04:34,970  -->  00:04:39,410
which means that our input data set only had 65 unique characters.

85

00:04:39,410  -->  00:04:41,950
Now, one final thing that I'll show to you is I'll

86

00:04:41,950  -->  00:04:44,770
show you the mapping between characters, and this is it.

87

